  - name: FACILITYHEADSURVEY_DICT.Q43_WARD_ALLOC
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>43. Has the health facility been implementing ward accommodation allocation since the UHC Act was passed in 2019 and was it a result of the UHC Act?</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals.)</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>Under UHC, basic ward allocation are as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals.) An health facility na tigimplementar para sa ward accommodaton allocation puon kan UHC Act na naipasa kan 2019 asin resulta ba kan UHC Act? (Laog ini sa UHC, basic ward allocation masunod: 90% kan sa government general hospital; 70% para sa government specialty hospitals asin10% para sa mga pribadong hospitals.)</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>Gipatuman na ba sa health facility ang ward accommodation allocation sukad naipasa ang UHC Act niadtong 2019, ug kini ba resulta sa maong balaod? (Ubos sa UHC, ang alokasyon sa basic ward mao ang mosunod: 90% para sa government general hospital; 70 para sa mga government specialty hospital; 10% para sa mga private hospital.)</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>Gipatuman ba sa health facility ang ward accommodation allocation sukad gipasar ang UHC Act sa 2019 ug tungod ba kini sa UHC Act? (Ubos sa UHC, ang basic ward allocation mao kining mosunod: 90% para sa mga pampublikong general hospital; 70% para sa mga pampublikong espesyalista nga hospital, ug 10% para sa mga pribadong hospital)</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>Nagpapatuman na ba an pasilidad panlawas hin pag-alotaga hin akomodasyon ha kwarto han pasyente tikang han pagpasa han UHC Act hadton 2019 ngan resulta ba ini han UHC Act? (Ha ilarum han UHC, an basik nga alokasyon han kwarto han pasyente amo an masunod: 90% para han mga pankabug-osan nga ospital han gobyerno; 70% para han mga espesyal nga ospital han gobyerno, ngan 10% para han mga pribado nga ospital.)</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
          HIL: |
            <p>Ang health facility nagapatuman bala sang ward accommodation allocation umpisa sang pag-aprobar sang UHC Act sang 2019, kag ini bala resulta sang UHC Act? (Sa idalum sang UHC, ang basic ward allocation amo ang masunod: 90% para sa government general hospitals; 70% para sa government specialty hospitals; kag 10% para sa private hospitals.)</p><p class="instruction">Under UHC, basic ward allocation is as follows: 90% for government general hospitals; 70% for government specialty hospitals, and 10% for private hospitals. DO NOT READ OPTIONS OUT LOUD. USE THE FOLLOWING GUIDE QUESTIONS TO PROBE. Has this been implemented? / Do you have this? Was this implemented before or after 2019? Was this implemented because of UHC? Do you plan to implement it in the next 1-2 years?</p>
